-- Oaxaca, Mexico, Governor Says 7 Reportedly Killed in Mudslide Are Alive
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2010-09-28T19:24:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/oaxaca-mexico-governor-says-7-reportedly-killed-in-mudslide-are-alive.html
The 7 people initially reported as
dead were found alive after a mudslide wiped out homes in rural
Oaxaca state, Governor Ulises Ruiz said.  An unknown number of people are missing, Ruiz said,
speaking in an interview on Radio Formula.  Earlier, Ruiz said that as many as 1,000 people were killed
in the village of Santa Maria Tlahuitoltepec.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
